      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>James Jackson Kilpatrick (1920- ), is former editor of the 
         <title render="italic">Richmond News Leader</title>,
         television commentator, author, and syndicated newspaper
         columnist.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>This collection consists of the additional papers of James
         J. Kilpatrick, ca. 1908, 1963-1997, including typescripts of
         his columns, "A Conservative View," "The Writer's Art and
         Covering the Courts," and "The Writer's Art," bound into
         volumes. Some of the typescripts have autographs changes and
         corrections and others are labeled "scanner ready copy."</p>
         <p>Other papers include reporter's notebooks, 1978-1994;
         publication agreement and correspondence with EPM
         Publications, chiefly regarding his book, 
         <title render="italic">The Foxes' Union</title>;
         correspondence and contract with Universal Press Syndicate
         concerning a weekly column discussing language, its usage, and
         the art of writing, and the eventual publication of his
         columns in book form, including two publicity photographs of
         Kilpatrick; correspondence with 
         <title render="italic">National Geographic Traveler</title>,
         concerning his travel story, "Richmond on The Noble James,"
         and the typescript of the story; papers pertaining to his
         participation in the Black-Eyed Pea Society of America; and
         correspondence with readers concerning his column, "The
         Writer's Art."</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement>
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged chronologically by subject.</p>
      </arrangement>
